# Start mowing in a specific area, ahead of the normal area-iteration order.
#
# `area` is the 0-based index into the working_areas list published by
# map_server_node. The behavior_tree_node sets it as the next target for
# GetNextUnmowedArea (which then mows that single area and stops, instead
# of iterating through all areas), and starts the mowing sequence by
# raising COMMAND_START internally.
#
# Returns success=true if the request was accepted; the actual mowing
# outcome is reported via /behavior_tree_node/high_level_status.
uint8 area
---
bool success
